[CWD is a transboundary disease as it is no
respecter of boundaries, whether they are
provinces or fences. If captive elk have had the
disease, it is likely at some point it will be
passed to wild cervids. Speculation is it may be
passed through urine which may explain its
transmission from captive to wild animals. - Mod.TG]

[A map of Saskatchewan may be seen at:
<http://www.canada-maps.org/saskatchewan-map.htm>
